---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="About - Junseo Choi"
  description="Learn more about Junseo Choi's research interests, academic background, and approach to computational linguistics and phonetics."
  pageTitle="About Me"
>
  <div class="about-content">
    <section class="bio-section">
      <h2>Who I Am</h2>
      <p>
        I am Junseo Choi, a researcher interested in <strong>experimental phonetics</strong>,
        <strong>acoustic phonetics</strong>, and <strong>computational linguistics</strong>.
        My work focuses on the computational analysis of speech and language data, with particular
        emphasis on prosody, L1-L2 speech comparison, and AI-based language learning applications.
      </p>
      <p>
        I combine rigorous linguistic analysis with modern computational methods to understand
        how humans produce and perceive speech, and how technology can support language learning
        and linguistic research.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="research-section">
      <h2>Research Interests</h2>
      <div class="interests-grid">
        <div class="interest-card">
          <h3>Experimental Phonetics</h3>
          <p>
            Designing and conducting controlled experiments to study speech production and
            perception phenomena across languages and populations.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="interest-card">
          <h3>Acoustic Phonetics</h3>
          <p>
            Analyzing the physical properties of speech signals to understand phonetic
            variation, prosodic patterns, and cross-linguistic differences.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="interest-card">
          <h3>Computational Linguistics</h3>
          <p>
            Applying computational methods and machine learning to linguistic data for
            analysis, modeling, and building language technology applications.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="interest-card">
          <h3>Speech Prosody</h3>
          <p>
            Investigating intonation, rhythm, stress, and timing patterns in speech, and
            their role in communication and language learning.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="interest-card">
          <h3>L1-L2 Speech Analysis</h3>
          <p>
            Comparing native and second-language speech patterns to understand language
            transfer, acquisition processes, and pedagogical implications.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="interest-card">
          <h3>AI for Language Learning</h3>
          <p>
            Developing AI-powered tools and applications to support language learners with
            personalized feedback, vocabulary acquisition, and pronunciation training.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="philosophy-section">
      <h2>Research Philosophy</h2>
      <p>
        I believe that effective linguistic research requires both theoretical rigor and
        practical applicability. My approach combines:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Empirical grounding:</strong> All claims should be supported by systematic
          observation and measurement of real linguistic data.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Methodological diversity:</strong> Different research questions require
          different methods, from controlled experiments to corpus analysis to computational modeling.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Interdisciplinary integration:</strong> The best insights often come from
          combining perspectives from linguistics, computer science, psychology, and education.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Application-oriented thinking:</strong> Research should not only advance
          theoretical understanding but also contribute to solving real-world language-related challenges.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="tools-section">
      <h2>Tools & Methods</h2>
      <p>In my research and development work, I regularly use:</p>

      <div class="tools-categories">
        <div class="tool-category">
          <h3>Programming & Analysis</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Python (NumPy, Pandas, scikit-learn, PyTorch)</li>
            <li>R (tidyverse, ggplot2)</li>
            <li>JavaScript/TypeScript</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-category">
          <h3>Phonetic Analysis</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Praat (scripting & automation)</li>
            <li>Parselmouth (Python interface to Praat)</li>
            <li>Speech signal processing libraries</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-category">
          <h3>AI & Machine Learning</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Large Language Models (OpenAI, Anthropic)</li>
            <li>Transformers & NLP frameworks</li>
            <li>Speech recognition & synthesis tools</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-category">
          <h3>Development & Deployment</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Modern web frameworks (Astro, React, Next.js)</li>
            <li>Version control (Git, GitHub)</li>
            <li>Cloud platforms & APIs</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta-section">
      <h2>Let's Connect</h2>
      <p>
        I'm always interested in discussing research ideas, potential collaborations, or
        questions about my work. Feel free to reach out!
      </p>
      <div class="cta-buttons">
        <a href="/contact" class="button">Get in Touch</a>
        <a href="/projects" class="button button-outline">View My Projects</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .about-content {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  section:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
  }

  .interests-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .interest-card {
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    padding: var(--space-md);
    transition: all var(--transition);
  }

  .interest-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .interest-card h3 {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .interest-card p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .philosophy-section ul {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .philosophy-section li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .philosophy-section li strong {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .tools-categories {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .tool-category h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .tool-category ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .tool-category li {
    padding: var(--space-xs) 0;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .tool-category li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .cta-section {
    text-align: center;
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .cta-section h2 {
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .cta-buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .button {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all var(--transition);
    background-color: var(--color-accent);
    color: white;
  }

  .button:hover {
    background-color: var(--color-accent-hover);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .button-outline {
    background-color: transparent;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    border: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
  }

  .button-outline:hover {
    background-color: var(--color-accent);
    color: white;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-content {
      font-size: var(--text-base);
    }

    .interests-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .tools-categories {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
